<!-- Hydro International -->
<section id="hydro" class="py-12 sm:py-16 bg-charcoal-900">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-8">
        <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
            <div class="text-accent-500 font-medium mb-2 text-sm">ENTERPRISE LEGACY MIGRATION</div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-3 sm:mb-4">Hydro International  - Internal Systems Modernisation</h2>
            <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-charcoal-200 max-w-3xl">
                Brought in to modernise Hydro International's internal project tracking systems ahead of a security audit. The platform consisted of a classic ASP application alongside an ageing Ruby on Rails system with growing operational risk.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 sm:gap-8 mb-8 sm:mb-12">
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE CHALLENGE</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100 text-sm sm:text-base">Years of accumulated technical debt, fragile behaviour, and security concerns made a direct rewrite risky. The business needed to pass audit requirements while keeping day-to-day operations running.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE APPROACH</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100 text-sm sm:text-base">Stabilised key issues first to reduce immediate pain. Introduced a new application in parallel and redirected traffic through it, progressively replacing pages and endpoints while delegating to the legacy system underneath. Functionality was migrated incrementally using a strangler-fig approach, removing legacy code as new equivalents were deployed and verified.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE OUTCOME</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100 text-sm sm:text-base">A smooth migration with minimal disruption. The resulting system reduced technical debt, met audit requirements, and gave the business a platform that was easier to change and maintain.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-3">KEY CAPABILITIES</div>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Legacy stabilisation</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Incremental migration</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Platform consolidation</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Matalan -->
<section id="matalan" class="py-12 sm:py-16 bg-charcoal-800">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-8">
        <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
            <div class="text-accent-500 font-medium mb-2 text-sm">LARGE-SCALE DATA MIGRATION</div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-3 sm:mb-4">Matalan  - Digital Asset Repository Migration</h2>
            <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-charcoal-200 max-w-3xl">
                Architected and delivered a large-scale migration of Matalan's image asset repository to a new platform provider, involving millions of images and complex metadata transformation.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 sm:gap-8 mb-8 sm:mb-12">
            <div class="bg-charcoal-700 border border-charcoal-600 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE CHALLENGE</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100 text-sm sm:text-base">The existing plan relied on a high-risk, 36-hour upload window with limited rollback options. Failure would have caused significant disruption.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-700 border border-charcoal-600 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE APPROACH</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100 text-sm sm:text-base">Designed a distributed ETL pipeline made up of small, focused services, each handling a single stage of the process. Stages ran in parallel, with clear checkpoints and idempotent operations to allow safe retries and rollbacks.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-700 border border-charcoal-600 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE OUTCOME</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100 text-sm sm:text-base">Millions of images migrated successfully in around 30 minutes. A risky one-off process was replaced with a fast, repeatable, and observable migration system.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-3">KEY CAPABILITIES</div>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">High-volume ETL</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Distributed systems</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Risk reduction</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Rent to Own -->
